---
import ContentPage from "../layouts/ContentPage.astro";

const orgSchema = JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "TMS List",
    "url": "https://tmslist.com",
    "description": "The leading directory of TMS therapy providers in the United States. Helping patients find FDA-cleared clinics with verified reviews and insurance information.",
    "foundingDate": "2024",
    "sameAs": [],
    "contactPoint": {
        "@type": "ContactPoint",
        "contactType": "customer service",
        "url": "https://tmslist.com/contact"
    },
    "areaServed": {
        "@type": "Country",
        "name": "United States"
    }
});
---

<ContentPage
    title="About TMS List"
    subtitle="Finding a TMS provider shouldn't be this hard. We're fixing that."
    description="TMS List helps people find FDA-cleared TMS therapy clinics with real reviews, real insurance info, and no guesswork. Learn why we built this."
    schema={orgSchema}
>
    <p>
        If you're here, you've probably already tried a few things that didn't work. Maybe antidepressants that dulled more than they helped. Maybe therapy that got you halfway there. And somewhere along the way, someone mentioned TMS.
    </p>
    <p>
        So you searched. And you found a mess — clinics with no reviews, insurance info buried three pages deep, and no way to tell who's actually good at this.
    </p>
    <p>
        That's why TMS List exists.
    </p>

    <h2>What we actually do</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Check the data:</strong> Every clinic listing includes verified device types, accepted insurance plans, and real patient ratings. We don't let clinics pay to hide bad reviews.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Explain the science — in English:</strong> TMS research is promising but dense. We break it down so you can have a real conversation with your doctor, not just nod along.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Fight for coverage:</strong> Too many insurers still make TMS approval harder than it should be. We publish which plans cover it, what they require, and how to push back when they say no.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who's behind this</h2>
    <p>
        TMS List was built by people who saw firsthand how hard it is to find good mental health care. We're not a clinic. We don't sell treatments. We make money when clinics pay for featured listings — but every clinic on the site, free or featured, goes through the same verification process.
    </p>
    <p>
        Right now we cover 900+ verified clinics across the US, with plans to expand into the UK, Canada, and Australia. If you're a provider who wants to be listed, or a patient who found a clinic that should be here, <a href="/contact">let us know</a>.
    </p>
</ContentPage>
